data.title: Don't waste your time or money!!!
data.text: Rude service, staff sit around while the bathrooms are disgusting.  The floors are dirty with food laying around.  Will not come back.

data.title: Happy Hour
data.text: JJ's is a great place to meet for happy hour. Our women's group have been meeting here for a few years and have been enjoying the summer weather on their expanded patio. Get there before 6:00 to enjoy the happy hour discounts. The appetizers are great!

data.title: Want To Like JJ's
data.text: Third time I've been here in a Sunday night with a group.   Wait staff has some improvement needed.   How hard is it to bring a menu?   And when one of our group asked if they had a wine menu, the waiter responded 'yes'.   Had to actually ask again for him to bring it over.   I really want to like this place...

data.title: Ignored
data.text: Stood by the hostess stand for 10 minutes.  The place was pretty empty and the hostess walked by numerous times serving the few that were there.  The bartender and some guy in a suit, maybe the manager, didn't acknowledge us either.  Finally went to a different restaurant down the road and had much better luck.  I can only assume they are going away soon and am anxious to see what takes it's place.

data.title: Great menu poorly trained staff
data.text:
We've tried multiple times but still come away disappointed. They have potential but still have room for improvement.  Especially with the front of the house staff. The best way to describe it, it's a coffee shop turned into a restaurant but no one trained the barista's their new duties.  

Service is tragically slow, and disjointed.  Here are some examples. Missing any greeting or welcome from the server.  Just "what would you like to drink?"  I'm not looking to make a new best friend but basic pleasantries are a sign of respect.  Serving a cup of coffee with cream but no spoon?  No silverware with the meal. No checking back for another beer when the first is empty? This is a loss of sale.  Bring out a plastic cup of milk for a child without a cover. This is a spill waiting to happen and it did.   Finally when walking back thru the restaurant from the patio my ever absent server asked if the signed copy was on the table.  No thank you, no come again, no pleasantries.  I waited tables for over ten years. I blame the management for not giving the tools for these servers to succeed. They don't know how to wait tables.  If it were busy this entire restaurant would of been a cluster.

data.title: It's a good place for coffe
data.text: A great place for quick meetings. Coffee and bakery are good.  But the bathroom is dirty. Staffs are ok.

data.title: Valentines
data.text: Enjoyed excellent service by a great waiter. Food was very very good for the abbreviated holiday menu.

data.title: Interesting burger choices but they aren't flavorful
data.text: They offer a variety of wines, beers and mixed drinks.  We tried a couple of the mixed drinks.  I had a jalapeno manga margarita that was good but probably too heavy on the jalapeno.  The jalapeno flavor was the dominant flavor with hints of mango. my husband had a cran-moji that he enjoyed. Their menu has offerings that are unusual and sound like they would be good.  We both opted for burgers.  I had the burger that had peanut butter, bacon and pine nuts.  I was really looking forward to it as last week I had gone to the Red Cow that had similar burger but with no pine nuts and an egg. The burger at JJ's was a bit of a disappointment.  First the entire thing crumbled when I cut it half but the main disappointment came from the meat itself had no flavor.  My husband had a different burger and he complained that the meat had no flavor. We both had fries with the burger.  They were okay but nothing special.  Mine were only warm rather than hot.  I don't need the extra calories so not eating them was an okay option for me.  JJ's may offer other food that is better but we won't be back to try it. The prices were just under $10 for drinks and burgers were about 12.  Our waitress was available but wait time for food and drinks was a little long.  The waitress listened and thanked us for feed back on the flavorless meat but no one else came to talk to us about the meal.

data.title: Rude service
data.text: I found the waiters at this place to be quite rude, and I don't intend to visit again. Very flippant, and dismissive.

data.title: Great Food, But Have Had Better Pasta
data.text:
We decided to try something new and stop at Jj's on a Friday night in hope of a new go-to restaurant in the area. Thankfully, this restaurant delivers and has plenty of great food to satisfy your eager taste buds.

Upon entering Jj's Coffee and Wine Bar for the first time, I was presented with an updated and friendly atmosphere. You will immediately feel at home once you step inside.

The service was very nice, but there a few slip ups here and there for not only us, but the folks sitting behind us. Although there were a few missteps, the staff was very pleasant and sparked up conversations. 

I ordered the Linguine with Chicken and was presented with a small bowl of pasta with a piece of garlic toast. At first I skeptical with the size of the entree, but the dish proved itself to be filling. The noodles themselves were good, but I have certainly had better in the South Metro area. The other people I was dining with said that their burgers were fantastic, so I'll definitely be back to munch on one of those puppies.

Jj's is definitely worth the stop whether you're going to dinner, lunch, or just having a few drinks at the bar. I'd recommend Jj's Coffee and Wine Bar to anyone living in the area.

data.title: Almost hate to tell people
data.text: how good this place is! Tucked away in the corner of a small commercial strip, you might not notice it as you drive by. Cozy ambiance: fireplace and comfortable sofas/chairs  plus booths and tables. Friendly service and good food (the fish tacos with lime mayo and slaw were yummy). The Happy Hour deals can't be beat.

data.title: Eden Prairies hidden gem!
data.text: I work nearby and found my new favorite spot!  This is the perfect place for a little happy hour on the patio or a date night for dinner! They offer top shelf liquor and have a wonderful menu for food. The cheese platter and caprese salad are my favorites, along with a dirty goose martini of course.  The salmon mac and cheese entree was wonderful, too! Some mornings, I like to go to the drivethru for a bacon, egg and cheese sandwich on an everything bagel. Will continue to come back!

data.title: Great wine, good food. Lovely ambiance
data.text: Great wine, good food. Lovely ambiance. Get there for happy hour to make it more worth your while - also love the live music!

data.title: Bad place
data.text: The food was good  the service awful   the trash was over flowing  in the bathrooms. The people  who works  there  didn't  care about the people  coming in  they were  so into the tv or co workers

data.title: Awful food and drinks
data.text: Visited this place when it 1st opened, and both the coffee and pastry we had were terrible!  Barista couldn't even make a decent simple Americano--it tasted weak and lacked aroma; the tapioca balls in the bubble tea were hard;  the pastry was almost stale tasting and hard and dry.  We thought it's because it's so new and just need to work out its kinks. Subsequently visited couple of more times to see if it has improved, as we would really enjoy having a nice coffee place in that area, and the decor of this place is pleasant enough.  Very disappointed!! Coffee and food --  still terrible!!  Will not go back .

data.title: Relaxing atmosphere, good food and wine
data.text: We had dinner on a Sunday night, amid a handful of others, mainly individuals with laptops and a hot beverage. The main course food options on Sunday night were limited to salads and sandwiches, but they were still fresh and delicious. A bottle of wine was half-priced, and we were able to take home what we didn't drink so we could finish it at home. A nice and relaxing place to grab Sunday dinner!

data.title: Great Coffee and Wine Bar
data.text: Fireplace, Great Barista's, quality, if limited, wine selections, booths and open tables, comfortable chairs and appetizer tables by the fireplace. Great after school event location whether its sports or fine arts!

data.title: Not so great...
data.text: With a limited menu, was hoping for something above average, but food and service was generally lousy.  Can you screw up a hamburger?  Answer is yes.  Asked for "pink", got "char-broiled".  Can you screw up french fries?  Apparently yes - somehow soggy.  Wife's chicken was edible, but the side of carrots was rock-hard.  After my bill was screwed up, I had to flag down the waitress after another 15 minutes because she totally forgot about us.  Maybe they can do wine and muffins, but stay away from dinner!

data.title: Great work spot
data.text: I am just leaving the most relaxing wine bar in the south metro. Great wine selection, amazing sandwiches, and top notch service!!

data.title: great place to stop & unwind over a great glass of wine
data.text: I enjoy going into JJ's! The wine list is good & the food is yummy! I just wish it were closer to my home so I could have this be my regular go to place!!
